<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="1151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.33112 RP/8–1045: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-10T17:00:00-03:00">August 10,
                                    1945—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>520. Bill on elimination Axis firms (despatch 6151, August 1<note n="91" xml:id="d1151fn91">Not printed.</note>) was presented to Congress
                            last night without change. Intervention is being enforced effectively
                            and will probably lead to liquidation of many firms before enactment
                            bill.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>